    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - REMOVE - OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The shifter housing must be removed to lock the transmission.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engage two (2) mainshaft synchronizers into two (2) mainshaft gears to lock the transmission
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302606">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302606" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302606" filename="../figg13/G1302606.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Engage Mainshaft Synchronizers into Mainshaft Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a large breaker bar or air impact wrench to remove the output shaft nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302607">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302607" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302607" filename="../figg13/G1302607.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Remove Output Shaft Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the yoke or flange straight to the rear and off the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302608">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302608" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302608" filename="../figg13/G1302608.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Pull Yoke or Flange to Rear and Off Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
